<span id="freeTextContainer10052414152654769015">The Adventures of Grandma Dowdel, part 2, is as good or better than Peck&apos;s first in this series, &quot;A Long Way from Chicago.&quot; As far as I&apos;m concerned, Grandma Dowdel is one of the most memorable characters in all of kids literature! Both she and this book are hysterically funny, heart-warming, clever, inspiring. Mary Alice&apos;s character develops beautifully here, as she learns and matures and adopts some of her grandmother&apos;s most endearing traits through her year living with her. I only wish Peck ha</span>
  <span id="freeText10052414152654769015" style="display:none">The Adventures of Grandma Dowdel, part 2, is as good or better than Peck's first in this series, "A Long Way from Chicago." As far as I'm concerned, Grandma Dowdel is one of the most memorable characters in all of kids literature! Both she and this book are hysterically funny, heart-warming, clever, inspiring. Mary Alice's character develops beautifully here, as she learns and matures and adopts some of her grandmother's most endearing traits through her year living with her. I only wish Peck had written ten more in this series.</span>
